{
  "stem": "21626.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had a Scottish teacher who studied and then taught at Prague University, for instance.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he spoke most abominable Czech.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I would have preferred his English with a Scottish accent.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But he prided himself as being one of the few who learned and mastered Czech, you know, to some degree.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Lots of the teachers we had were really too good to teach us grammar school children because they were of university caliber.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were professors in their, in their civil life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But you see, the school had a dual purpose.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was used by members of the forces to take their matriculation during their leave.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And of course, they had to have their matriculation to, to, be made into a-- for there to be an officer.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So, so for their advancement, they studied and, and came to the school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was actually very strange to see these men, particularly the airmen, who perhaps fought in the Battle of Britain and were so brave.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there they were trembling at the knees because they were taking an exam, you know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And I also remember because food was so hard to come by-- meat particularly-- and we all gave up our weekly rations for these men who were our heroes, who were fighting for our freedom, you know, so that they could have a good feed, because we had a superb, superb cook, who could make a feast out of almost anything.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Very little, because you see, there was a, a point of dispute before we were accepted on the transports.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after-- in fact, before the Germans marched in, but after Sudetenland was taken over, our parents had the whole family christened-- or baptized, I should say.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
